You did. You made your point clearly last time.

512
00:39:04,220 --> 00:39:08,160
Today, it's time for me to make mine.

513
00:39:10,740 --> 00:39:13,930
All right. Say it.

514
00:39:14,980 --> 00:39:17,350
I've thought it through.

515
00:39:17,350 --> 00:39:22,000
I don't mind if you love the boy.

516
00:39:23,110 --> 00:39:25,520
What do you mean, "You don't mind"?

517
00:39:25,520 --> 00:39:29,510
The point is that you're the best candidate for me to marry.

518
00:39:29,510 --> 00:39:33,189
It's a win-win situation if we get married.

519
00:39:33,190 --> 00:39:37,810
It's good for you too.

520
00:39:41,670 --> 00:39:44,280
I don't understand what you mean.

521
00:39:44,990 --> 00:39:47,480
With the help of Luquan Group,

522
00:39:47,480 --> 00:39:52,620
it will be easy for the Poseidon Department Store to become yours.

523
00:39:54,580 --> 00:39:57,220
You are just looking for a puppet.

524
00:39:57,970 --> 00:40:00,730
Not just anyone can be my puppet, okay?

525
00:40:00,730 --> 00:40:05,270
After we marry, you're free to fall in love with anyone.

526
00:40:05,270 --> 00:40:09,420
We won't interfere with each other. We'll have our own happiness.

527
00:40:11,850 --> 00:40:14,650
You mean contracting a marriage.

528
00:40:15,300 --> 00:40:20,450
But I'm telling you, marriage is sacred to me.

529
00:40:20,450 --> 00:40:24,869
I will never recognize marriage as a business.

530
00:40:24,870 --> 00:40:29,030
Why not? We'll both get what we need.

531
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:32,520
Many friends of mine have done the same.

532
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:34,620
Wow.

533
00:40:34,620 --> 00:40:37,899
Your upper class logic is truly amazing.

534
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:40,319
I'm just an ordinary guy so leave me alone.

535
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:43,329
I will never accept a fake relationship.

536
00:40:43,330 --> 00:40:48,200
Especially... I won't marry someone I don't love.

537
00:40:58,090 --> 00:41:00,940
CEO? CEO!

538
00:41:00,940 --> 00:41:02,579
Let's go report for duty.

539
00:41:02,580 --> 00:41:04,600
For what?

540
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:07,049
It's for a job, of course.

541
00:41:07,050 --> 00:41:10,870
You've never applied for a job. How did you get it, and why must I go there?

542
00:41:10,870 --> 00:41:12,909
Don't ask. Just come with me.

543
00:41:12,910 --> 00:41:16,719
No. I just got my delivery job back.

544
00:41:16,719 --> 00:41:18,449
Just quit the job.

545
00:41:18,450 --> 00:41:22,530
Again? What if the place you work at isn't reliable?

546
00:41:22,530 --> 00:41:24,640
Don't you trust me?

547
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:26,290
That's true. I don't.

548
00:41:26,290 --> 00:41:30,160
All right. Forget it. I'll go by myself.

549
00:41:31,700 --> 00:41:33,950
He shows all his emotions on his face.

550
00:41:33,950 --> 00:41:36,349
He'll make mistakes if he goes alone.

551
00:41:36,350 --> 00:41:38,379
No. I have to go and watch him.

552
00:41:38,380 --> 00:41:40,050
Hai Yi.

553
00:41:40,050 --> 00:41:42,230
[Poseidon Department Store]

554
00:41:57,490 --> 00:41:59,259
From today onward,

555
00:41:59,260 --> 00:42:03,360
are we Customer Service Department staff at Poseidon Department Store?

556
00:42:03,360 --> 00:42:07,590
Didn't Director Tseng say we could start working from today?

557
00:42:07,590 --> 00:42:10,270
It's way too easy.

558
00:42:12,110 --> 00:42:16,450
Do you think they'll find out we live in their warehouse?

559
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:19,560
Don't worry. It's an old one. It's not in use now.

560
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:23,530
Also, we've lived there for a while, and no one has come by, right?

561
00:42:23,530 --> 00:42:27,050
Come. Here are your badges.

562
00:42:27,050 --> 00:42:29,440
Welcome to Poseidon Department Store.

563
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:34,290
Thank you, Director Tseng. We will definitely work hard and do our best.

564
00:42:38,370 --> 00:42:41,670
Very nice. Very energetic.

565
00:42:41,670 --> 00:42:44,060
Which ones are our desks?

566
00:42:44,060 --> 00:42:46,600
How about those two?

567
00:42:47,310 --> 00:42:49,330
Thank you, Director Tseng.

568
00:42:51,110 --> 00:42:56,390
Hai Yi... May we talk privately?

569
00:42:56,390 --> 00:42:58,990
- Sure. Where do you want to talk?
- Right here is fine.

570
00:42:58,990 --> 00:43:01,550
Can you lower yourself down?

571
00:43:02,230 --> 00:43:04,970
A bit lower.

572
00:43:07,000 --> 00:43:10,360
That's right. This height is just about right.

573
00:43:11,010 --> 00:43:16,500
May I ask if you're related to our chairman?

574
00:43:16,500 --> 00:43:18,870
"Hai" is a rare family name.

575
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:21,300
You're overthinking, Director Tseng. It's just a coincidence.

576
00:43:21,300 --> 00:43:23,470
If I was really related to the chairman,

577
00:43:23,470 --> 00:43:27,060
I wouldn't have had to work for a junior position.

578
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:31,270
Right. I'll leave you to work.

579
00:43:42,170 --> 00:43:44,250
What did Director Tseng say to you?

580
00:43:44,250 --> 00:43:46,270
He simply encouraged me.

581
00:43:46,860 --> 00:43:50,410
I knew he was a good guy. We are so lucky.

582
00:43:50,410 --> 00:43:53,590
It feels like a dream to me.

583
00:43:53,590 --> 00:43:55,590
I've studied hard since I was young,

584
00:43:55,590 --> 00:43:58,140
so I could get into a big company and earn a lot of money.

585
00:43:58,140 --> 00:44:03,080
I didn't expect to fulfill my dream in this era.

586
00:44:03,740 --> 00:44:09,000
Hai Yi, thank you. Let's do our best together.

587
00:44:25,350 --> 00:44:28,409
It's really different to work at a big company.

588
00:44:28,410 --> 00:44:30,880
Everything looks nice.

589
00:44:39,940 --> 00:44:43,480
Dai Zhe-ni. Why are you here?

590
00:44:46,180 --> 00:44:49,250
Hey... You've become staff at Poseidon Department Store too?

591
00:44:49,250 --> 00:44:53,450
Surprise? Shock? Happy?

592
00:44:53,450 --> 00:44:55,149
You've never mentioned this before.

593
00:44:55,150 --> 00:44:58,980
I didn't expect it either. We're co-workers from now on.

594
00:44:58,980 --> 00:45:01,739
I look forward to learning from you.

595
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:03,550
I'll teach you depending on your performance.

596
00:45:03,550 --> 00:45:06,380
Are you free now?

597
00:45:06,380 --> 00:45:10,510
I'll buy you lunch.

598
00:45:10,510 --> 00:45:12,100
Let's go.

599
00:45:12,790 --> 00:45:14,940
Lin Huai-en. We need you to be at the cold storage.

600
00:45:14,940 --> 00:45:17,699
Go help check the stocks.

601
00:45:17,699 --> 00:45:20,950
- Now?
- Yes. Right now.

602
00:45:20,950 --> 00:45:22,860
Okay.

603
00:45:22,860 --> 00:45:26,840
Sorry. I've got to work now. I'll catch up with you later.

604
00:45:26,840 --> 00:45:30,650
All right. Well... Text me.

605
00:45:30,650 --> 00:45:33,030
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

606
00:45:49,660 --> 00:45:52,430
Can anyone open the door for me?

607
00:45:55,470 --> 00:45:59,260
Anyone? Can anyone open the door for me?

608
00:46:20,130 --> 00:46:23,740
Hsuan, Lin Huai-en is locked in the cold storage.

609
00:46:23,740 --> 00:46:25,729
What if something goes wrong?

610
00:46:25,730 --> 00:46:29,470
Just leave it. He offended Manager Tony.

611
00:46:29,470 --> 00:46:31,290
Get out of my way.

612
00:46:38,520 --> 00:46:42,480
Huai-en. Huai-en.

613
00:46:42,480 --> 00:46:45,760
Huai-en, are you in there? Huai-en?

614
00:46:48,780 --> 00:46:52,290
Huai-en. Huai-en.

615
00:46:53,690 --> 00:46:55,200
Huai-en.

